When you have sticky scroll enabled in VS and are scrolling into a c# extension block, the extension line doesn't appear in the sticky scroll margin, see this screenshot:

<img width="900" height="150" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/72579d5a-85ba-4416-add1-970e22446aed" />

for this code:
```cs
public static class DictionaryExtensions
{
  extension<TKey, TValue>(Dictionary<TKey, TValue> dict)
  {
     public async Task<TValue> GetOrAddAsync(TKey key, Func<TKey, Task<TValue>> factory)
    {
        if (!dict.TryGetValue(key, out var value))
        {
            value = await factory(key);
            dict[key] = value;
        }
        return value;
    }
```

**Expected Behavior**:
the extension block should appear as a line in sticky scroll
**Actual Behavior**:
it doesn't, so you don't know which extension block the current method is in, nor, which parameters are there.

